<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6970ff3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12131"><num value="12131">§ 12131.</num><heading> Command of documented vessels</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6970ff4-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12131/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">In General</inline>.—</heading><content>Except as provided in subsection (b), a documented vessel may be placed under the command only of a citizen or noncitizen national (as such term is described in section 308 of the Immigration and Nationality Act (<ref href="/us/usc/t8/s1408">8 U.S.C. 1408</ref>)) of the United States.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6970ff5-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12131/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Exceptions</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>Subsection (a) does not apply to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6970ff6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12131/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a vessel with only a recreational endorsement; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6970ff7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12131/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> an unmanned barge operating outside of the territorial waters of the United States.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6970ff8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s5">Pub. L. 109–304, § 5</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1505">120 Stat. 1505</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/181/dC/tXXXV/s3529/a/3">Pub. L. 110–181, div. C, title XXXV, § 3529(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="2008-01-28">Jan. 28, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/603">122 Stat. 603</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXIII/s7301/b/2/C">Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXIII, § 7301(b)(2)(C)</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1752">139 Stat. 1752</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
